cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper discusses deep reinforcement learning for robotics tasks, which falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The focus on learning from fixed datasets suggests a strong emphasis on machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of exploration methods and continuous control tasks also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the use of a real robot arm suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
